# Implementation workflow

Any code change follows **steps 1–6**. The user approves at **step 3 only** (the plan), not implementation diffs.

**Start:** Plan mode before step 1. No code until explicit step 3 approval.

## Steps

| Step | Mode | Action | Gate |
| ---- | ---- | ------ | ---- |
| **1** | Plan | Scope, files, exit commands, clean-break checks; link checklist rows. Plan file: `~/.cursor/plans/<task>_*.md` only (not in-repo). | — |
| **2** | Plan | Pre-impl review (`code-reviewer`, readonly): trim scope; favor simplicity; DX if user-facing; **Deferred** for cuts. Revise plan; **no code**. | Scope trimmed; plan favors simplicity; exits set; **Deferred** if anything cut; plan stand-alone; incremental edits keep **previous plan** |
| **3** | Plan → Agent | Present plan; wait for approval; roadmap ask if **Deferred** (below). | Roadmap ask if **Deferred**; explicit approval |
| **4** | Agent | Run exit tests/commands; fix failures. No extra confirmation prompts. | — |
| **5** | Agent | Post-impl review vs approved plan + [clean break](docs/roadmap/engineering/v1-implementation-checklist.md#clean-break-policy-v1--no-legacy-path). | Diff matches plan; no legacy creep |
| **6** | Agent | Fix blocking findings; re-test; update [CODE.md](CODE.md) (topic sections only), checklist `[x]`, [CLAUDE.md](CLAUDE.md) if needed. | Blocking fixes; durable lessons → CODE.md |

Before step 4: reread [CODE.md](CODE.md). Boundaries: [CODE.md — what belongs](CODE.md#what-belongs-here); clean break: checklist + [CODE.md — packaging](CODE.md#packaging-and-clean-break).

## Step 2 — Plan review

**Goals:** Smaller scope; simplicity (design, APIs, diffs); better user-facing DX — without telegram-style compression.

| Lens | When relevant |
| ---- | ------------- |
| **Time-to-results** | Fewer commands to first green; mock/no-key path in exits |
| **Ceremony vs value** | Extend existing YAML/CLI; drop boilerplate that does not buy gate/regression value |
| **Errors & discoverability** | Failures name the fix (path, flag, field); examples/README in-plan when behavior changes |
| **Spikes** | Comparative claims → [spike-dx-competitive-analysis.md](docs/roadmap/research/spike-dx-competitive-analysis.md) A–C; split orchestration vs domain |

DX vs minimal scope / simplicity → **record tradeoff** in plan (default: smaller scope and simpler shape unless user asked for DX).

**Deferred:** One line per cut (what + why). Never silently drop user- or spike-requested work.

**Plan quality (step 3):** Full sentences; explicit scope, files, exits, rationale. After feedback: revise **incrementally** in the same file; keep **previous plan**; state what changed. Current plan must **stand alone**.

## Step 3 — Approval

Stop and wait for the user.

**Deferred → roadmap:** If **Deferred** is non-empty, ask where to park items **before** approval. Do not edit roadmap docs until the user answers; record choice in the plan (`Phase N` / `ADOPT-00x` / spike note / none). Update roadmap in-session only on yes.

| Target | Use for |
| ------ | ------- |
| [v1-implementation-checklist.md](docs/roadmap/engineering/v1-implementation-checklist.md) | Phase row or post-v1 follow-up |
| [adoption-usability-backlog.md](docs/roadmap/research/adoption-usability-backlog.md) | ADOPT ergonomics / adoption |
| Spike / research notes | DX or dogfood deferrals |

| User response | Next |
| ------------- | ---- |
| Feedback / change request | → step 2: vs CODE.md, checklist, ADRs, codebase; accept, push back, or smaller alternative; record in plan or ADR; re-run pre-impl review; preserve **previous plan**. No code. |
| Explicit approval | Reread CODE.md; Agent mode; step 4. |

Repeat **2 → 3** until explicit approval.

## After close

Optionally remind: `/summarize` to compact context (user-initiated).
